-- MOVES-Standard Chartered hires four analyst to its equity research team 
-- By Anet Josline Pinto in Bangalore
-- Tue Oct 07, 2014 09:00AM EDT
-- None



Oct 7 (Reuters) - Standard Chartered Plc <STAN.L> hires four analysts to its consumer and industrial equity research teams in Hong Kong and Korea.

Tina Li and Byun Seong-Jin joined in August to cover the industrial sector, and Lee Jiyeon and Jessica Hong joined in July and September, respectively, to cover the consumer sector, the bank said. Li and Hong will be based in Hong Kong and report to Erwin Sanft, head of China and Hong Kong equity research; while Lee and Byun will be based in Seoul and report to Chung Sun, head of Korea equity research. Li will lead coverage of the automotive and capital goods sectors in China. She joins from BNP Paribas <BNPP.PA> where she covered the same sectors. Byun will cover the Korean steel, shipbuilding, engineering and construction sectors and joins after 15 years at Mirae Asset Securities where he most recently led the industrial team. Lee will cover the Korean consumer sector and joins from KB Investment & Securities where she was responsible for cosmetics, retail and telecommunications sectors.